###############################################
# TESTING CHECKLIST
###############################################

### ? Before Running Tests:
# 1. Make sure application is running: dotnet run
# 2. Get valid JWT token and replace "YOUR_TOKEN_HERE"
# 3. Ensure PostgreSQL is running
# 4. Have a SQL client ready (pgAdmin, DBeaver, etc.)

### ? Test Execution Order:
# 1. Run S1: Create Product
# 2. Run S2: Create 2 Variants
# 3. Execute SQL Check Point 1 ? Verify 2 variant replicas
# 4. Run S3: Create Inventories
# 5. Execute SQL Check Point 2 ? Verify 2 inventory replicas
# 6. Run S4: Create 3 Prices
# 7. Execute SQL Check Point 3 ? Verify 3 price replicas
# 8. Run S5: Create 3 Price Details
# 9. Execute SQL Check Point 4 ? Verify 3 price detail replicas
# 10. Run S6: Update Variant/Inventory/Price/PriceDetail
# 11. Execute all verify queries ? Confirm updates synced
# 12. Execute Final Verification SQL ? See complete picture

### ? Success Criteria:
# ? All API calls return 2xx status codes
# ? SQL queries return expected number of rows
# ? Replica data matches source data
# ? Updates are reflected in replicas
# ? No exceptions in application logs

